, Japan and South Korea from sitting down together to talk about Northeast Asian integration, and wider Asian integration. Another example is the question of comfort women. Former Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe's statement - that there is no evidence that Japan's government or army forced women to work in military brothels during the War - appeared to go back on a 1993 apology for the comfort women. How such issues of history are dealt with by countries of this region has an effect on contemporary relations among the major powers contending for leadership in East Asia.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aWorld War, 1939-1945--East Asia--Congresses. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945--South Asia--Congresses. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945--Southeast Asia--Congresses. 7aHISTORY / Military / World War II.2bisacsh1 aChandler, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDatta-Ray, Sunanda K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGungwu, Wang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarper, Tim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHorvat, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIleto, Reynaldo C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aInoguchi, Takashi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJianli, Huang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKesavapany, K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKheng, Cheah Boon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKoh, David, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLatif, Asad-ul Iqbal, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeirissa, Richard Z., 